node.text: On the occasion of Chinese New Year, Pulitzer Prize-winning author @iandenisjohnson invites readers through the magnificent and storied palace built by China’s Yongle Emperor to serve as the seat of the Ming dynasty in #ForbiddenCity, the latest addition to Assouline’s Ultimate Collection. #ChineseNewYear

node.title: Forbidden City: The Palace at the Heart of Chinese Culture

node.title: The Creation of the Ultimate Collection

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by ASSOULINE on August 24, 2021 tagging @jaegerlecoultre, and @n_foulkes.

node.text:
The Jaeger-LeCoultre Reverso, with its unique reversible case, has evolved through nine decades, continually reinventing itself while never compromising its identity – becoming a classic of 20th-century design and still to this day epitomizing the spirit of modernity. Jaeger-LeCoultre: Reverso, a mesmerizing title for the premier watch lover.

#JaegerLeCoultre @n_foulkes. 
📸 @jaegerlecoultre

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ASSOULINE in Karakalpak Savitsky Museum / Muzey Savitskogo with @assoulineyaffa, @zelfiratregulova, and @haraldgottschalkphotography. May be art of nature and tree.
Photo shared by ASSOULINE on August 21, 2021 tagging @guillaume_plisson, @mimcain, @yachtaporter, and @seacloudcruises. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'CLOUD'.

node.text:
Whether impossible in sheer size, speed, luxurious features or advanced technology, all the vessels in this fantasy marina have transformed the yachting seascape. Built in 1931 and still sailing around the world, the schooner Sea Cloud is unique by its master suite has an ornate, post-Victorian look, complete with travel chests. 

#Yachts @yachtaporter @mimcain @guillaume_plisson @seacloudcruises
📸© Sea Cloud Cruises

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by ASSOULINE on August 20, 2021 tagging @guillaume_plisson, @mimcain, and @yachtaporter.

node.text:
Yachts: The Impossible Collection, a visual history showing the incredible evolution of the yachting scene and creations of the beautiful and impossible creatures that break the boundaries of technology, luxury and decadence.

#Yachts @yachtaporter @mimcain @guillaume_plisson

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by ASSOULINE on August 19, 2021 tagging @assoulineyaffa, and @haraldgottschalkphotography.

node.text:
Art collector Igor Vitalyevich Savitsky dedicated his life to saving the world’s most important works of Russian avant-garde art, which would have otherwise disappeared forever. Uzbekistan: Avant-Garde Orientalists is a celebration of the near-forgotten collection now displayed at the Nukus Museum.

@assoulineyaffa @haraldgottschalkphotography
